article_text:
March 29, 2016 06:22 AM

Police in Irondequoit are searching for a robbery suspect Tuesday morning after an overnight robbery.

The robbery happened at the 7-Eleven on Titus Avenue just before 11 Monday night. Investigators say a man demanded money from the store clerk and was given $56. Police say the man ran from the scene and that no weapons were used.
